Package org.opensextant.giscore.input.kml

Interface KmlReader.ImportEventHandler

Enclosing class:
KmlReader
public static interface KmlReader.ImportEventHandler
ImportEventHandler interface used for callers to implement handling of GISObjects encountered as NetworkLinks are parsed. If the callback handleEvent() method returns false then recursion is aborted no more NetworkLink features are processed. 
 KmlReader reader = new KmlReader(new URL(
   "..."))
 ... // read all features from reader
 reader.close();
 // reader stream must be closed (all features processed) before trying
 // to import features from NetworkLinks.
 reader.importFromNetworkLinks(
    new KmlReader.ImportEventHandler() {
          public boolean handleEvent(UrlRef ref, IGISObject gisObj)
       {
            // do something with gisObj
            return true;
       }
       public void handleError(URI uri, Exception e) {
           // optionally do something with exceptions
       }
    });

  • Method Details

    • handleEvent

      boolean handleEvent(UrlRef ref, IGISObject gisObj)
      The KmlReader will invoke this method for each GISObject encountered during parsing. All elements will be reported in document order. Return false to abort importing features from network links.
      Parameters:
      ref - UriRef for NetworkLink resource
      gisObj - new IGISObject object. This will never be null.
      Returns:
      Return true to continue parsing and recursively follow NetworkLinks, false stops following NetworkLinks.

      Parameters:

      e - Exception thrown
